description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting and appealing opportunity has arisen within the Gynaecology Department at Guy&#39;s and St Thomas&#39; NHS Foundation Trust for an Assistant Service Manager. The role is ideal for candidates that are looking for a challenge and an opportunity to make a positive and impactful contribution to the service. Candidates who are interested must have a proactive approach, excellent organisation and time management skills, written and verbal communication skills, and be a team player with a collaborative approach and a can-do attitude at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for the day-to-day running of the outpatient service including the line management of 9 administrative staff. This role will involve the line management of staff, overseeing daily clinics ensuring maximum utilisation of clinics, ensuring patients have a positive experience when attending the outpatients department, validation of the PTL, rota management and other administrative duties. In addition, the post holder must be willing to undertake any audits/projects to assist the team when necessary, in conjunction with the Service Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePratiksha PatelJob titleService ManagerEmail addressPratiksha.patel@gstt.nhs.ukTelephone number020 7188 3681Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal conversations/visits can be arranged after shortlisting has been completed by contacting Pratiksha Patel, Service Manager for Gynaecology via email Pratiksha.patel@gstt.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
